rint of the dual release. The next slide (fitness data) shows that Path A (concordant_strong, n=32) is marginally enriched for envelope-stress phenotypes (fold 1.60×, p=0.016) while Path B (buffered) is not — sharpening which arm carries the operative Layer-1 fitness signal.\",\n  \"evidence_anchors\": [\n    {\"kind\": \"report_section\", \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §Finding 1\"},\n    {\"kind\": \"report_section\", \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §NB01 — Leaden 2018 Fur signature\"}\n  ],\n  \"revision_log\": [\n    {\n      \"revised_at\": \"2026-06-07T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"finding_id\": \"F003\",\n      \"finding_class\": \"claim_evidence\",\n      \"summary\": \"Replaced NB00 sphingolipid heatmap (S3 content misplaced in the S1 R-slide slot) with the NB01 Fur–Leaden concordance scatter (figures/NB01_fur_signature_scatter.png); rewrote title to lead with ρ=0.315/71%/93-DEG anchor statistics per REPORT §Finding 1; rewrote caption to name the concordant_strong vs buffered partition per REPORT §NB01 image caption and scatter description; updated data_source and evidence_anchors accordingly.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":17998,"cache_read_input_tokens":44485,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":17998},"output_tokens":17,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7dbc6ac5-2e22-4737-9cd1-cf751888377b","uuid":"79774485-1499-4759-bccd-be79a3ad2619"}
