{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011eNn7E9Edu5b16oCX44QQV","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t{\n2\t  \"id\": 7,\n3\t  \"position\": 7,\n4\t  \"substory_id\": \"S1\",\n5\t  \"layout\": \"data_figure\",\n6\t  \"content\": {\n7\t    \"title\": \"NB01: Δfur derepression concordant with Leaden 2018 — and amplified (ρ=0.315, p=2.08e-03)\",\n8\t    \"figure\": \"figures/NB01_fur_signature_scatter.png\",\n9\t    \"caption\": \"Leaden 2018 Δfur logFC (x) vs our 4584-vs-4580 logFC (y), 93 DEGs. Concordant_strong (blue) top-right, exceeding Leaden's amplitude; buffered cbb3/fix set (orange) near y=0; HutA at (+10.5, +2.2) is the most extreme point.\",\n10\t    \"data_source\": \"REPORT.md §Finding 1; NB 01_leaden2018_fur_signature.ipynb cell 5\"\n11\t  },\n12\t  \"speaker_notes_seed\": \"This scatter is the S1 punchline figure. The x-axis is Leaden 2018's Δfur logFC for 93 published Δfur DEGs; the y-axis is our 4584-vs-4580 logFC for those same genes. Spearman ρ=0.315 (p=2.08e-03) and 71% sign concordance confirm that Fur derepression is a genuine component of our signal — we are seeing the canonical Fur regulon. The critical observation is the asymmetry: the concordant_strong cluster (dark blue, top-right) is amplified — our logFCs exceed Leaden's. HutA, the archetypal iron-derepressed TBDT, lands at our +10.5 vs Leaden's +2.2. The orange cluster (buffered cbb3/fix respiratory operon) sits near y=0 despite Leaden's -5 to -9 range — the SspB co-deletion is blunting that arm. This one panel sets up both findings that follow: Path A (concordant_strong, n=32) will test fitness enrichment; Path B (buffered, n=26) will fail enrichment against the 33.25% genome background.\",\n13\t  \"evidence_anchors\": [\n14\t    {\"kind\": \"report_section\", \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §Finding 1\"},\n15\t    {\"kind\": \"report_section\", \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §NB01 — Leaden 2018 Fur signature\"}\n16\t  ],\n17\t  \"revision_log\": [\n18\t    {\n19\t      \"revis