aption to name explicit n-counts (n=32, n=53) and the Leaden logFC range (–5 to –9) grounded in REPORT §Finding 1 and §NB01; updates speaker_notes_seed with Path A/B fitness preview bridging to the next slide.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":4,"oldLines":12,"newStart":4,"newLines":12,"lines":["   \"substory_id\": \"S1\",","   \"layout\": \"data_figure\",","   \"content\": {","-    \"title\": \"NB01: Δfur derepression concordant with Leaden 2018 — and amplified (ρ=0.315, p=2.08e-03)\",","+    \"title\": \"Fur–Leaden concordance: ρ=0.315, 71% sign agreement across 93 DEGs — and a buffered respiratory cluster at y≈0\",","     \"figure\": \"figures/NB01_fur_signature_scatter.png\",","-    \"caption\": \"Leaden 2018 Δfur logFC (x) vs our 4584-vs-4580 logFC (y), 93 DEGs. Concordant_strong (blue) top-right, exceeding Leaden's amplitude; buffered cbb3/fix set (orange) near y=0; HutA at (+10.5, +2.2) is the most extreme point.\",","-    \"data_source\": \"REPORT.md §Finding 1; NB 01_leaden2018_fur_signature.ipynb cell 5\"","+    \"caption\": \"Concordant_strong genes (dark blue, n=32) populate the top-right quadrant; buffered cbb3/fix/cyd genes (orange, n=53) cluster near y=0 despite Leaden logFC –5 to –9. HutA at +10.5 (ours) vs +2.2 (Leaden) anchors the amplified derepression signal.\",","+    \"data_source\": \"REPORT.md §Finding 1; notebooks/01_leaden2018_fur_signature.ipynb cell 5\"","   },","-  \"speaker_notes_seed\": \"This scatter is the S1 punchline figure. The x-axis is Leaden 2018's Δfur logFC for 93 published Δfur DEGs; the y-axis is our 4584-vs-4580 logFC for those same genes. Spearman ρ=0.315 (p=2.08e-03) and 71% sign concordance confirm that Fur derepression is a genuine component of our signal — we are seeing the canonical Fur regulon. The critical observation is the asymmetry: the concordant_strong cluster (dark blue, top-right) is amplified — our logFCs exceed Leaden's. HutA, the archetypal iron-derepressed TBDT, lands at our +10.5 vs Leaden's +2.2. The orange cluster (buffered cbb3/fix respiratory operon) sits near y=0 despite Leaden's -5 to -9 range — the SspB co-deletion is blunting that arm. This one panel sets up both findings that follow: Path A (concordant_strong, n=32) will test fitness enrichment; Path B (buffered, n=26) will fail enrichment against the 33.25% genome background.\",","+  \"speaker_notes_seed\": \"The NB01 scatter is the backbone of Layer 1: x-axis is Leaden 2018 Δfur logFC (published Caulobacter Δfur-only signature); y-axis is our 4584-vs-4580 contrast (Δfur ΔsspB ΔrsaA vs ΔrsaA). Spearman ρ=0.315 (p=2.08e-03) over 93 shared DEGs confirms Fur derepression as a major driver of our signal. Two populations dominate: concordant_strong genes (dark blue, n=32, top-right quadrant) are the operative Fur-released transporters and TBDTs; HutA is the extreme anchor point at our +10.5 vs Leaden's +2.2 — our strain amplifies the derepression. The buffered set (orange, n=53) is the key subplot: these cbb3/cyd/fix-NOPQ micro-aerobic respiratory genes are strongly derepressed in Leaden's Δfur-alone background but stay near y=0 in our Δfur ΔsspB combined background — the SspB arm is buffering them at the transcript level. Delivery note: the buffered cluster is not a weakness; it is the mechanistic fingerprint of the dual release. The next slide (fitness data) shows that Path A (concordant_strong, n=32) is marginally enriched for envelope-stress phenotypes (fold 1.60×, p=0.016) while Path B (buffered) is not — sharpening which arm carries the operative Layer-1 fitness signal.\",","   \"evidence_anchors\": [","     {\"kind\": \"report_section\", \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §Finding 1\"},","     {\"kind\": \"report_section\", \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §NB01 — Leaden 2018 Fur signature\"}"]},{"oldStart":20,"oldLines":6,"newStart":20,"newLines":12,"lines":["       \"finding_id\": \"F003\",","       \"finding_class\": \"substory_arc\",","       \"summary\": \"Replaced wrong-layer sphingolipid heatmap (00_sphingolipid_locus_heatmap.png, Layer 3 content duplicating slide 16/S3) with NB01 Fur-Leaden concordance scatter (NB01_fur_signature_scatter.png) as the S1 Layer-1 R-slide punchline figure (ρ=0.315, p=2.08e-03, 71% concordance, 93 DEGs); content replacement applied instead of canonical position-swap because the structural defect was wrong content occupying the S1 R-slide slot, not wrong slide position; slide 7 remains at position 7 in S1.\"","+    },","+    {","+      \"revised_at\": \"2026-06-07T00:00:00Z\",","+      \"finding_id\": \"F003\",","+      \"finding_class\": \"claim_evidence\",","+      \"summary\": \"Second-attempt pass: prior revision correctly replaced the figure but left a topic-label title ('NB01: Δfur derepression concordant with Leaden 2018 — and amplified') and recorded the wrong finding_class (substory_arc). This pass rewrites the title to claim form per fix_hint ('Fur–Leaden concordance: ρ=0.315, 71% sign agreement across 93 DEGs — and a buffered respiratory cluster at y≈0'); upgrades the caption to name explicit n-counts (n=32, n=53) and the Leaden logFC range (–5 to –9) grounded in REPORT §Finding 1 and §NB01; updates speaker_notes_seed with Path A/B fitness preview bridging to the next slide.\"","     }","   ]"," }"]}],"originalFile":"{\n  \"id\": 7,\n  \"position\": 7,\n  \"substory_id\": \"S1\",\n  \"layout\": \"data_figure\",\n  \"content\": {\n    \"title\": \"NB01: Δfur derepression concordant with Leaden 2018 — and amplified (ρ=0.315, p=2.08e-03)\",\n    \"figure\": \"figures/NB01_fur_signature_scatter.png\",\n    \"caption\": \"Leaden 2018 Δfur logFC (x) vs our 4584-vs-4580 logFC (y), 93 DEGs. Concordant_strong (blue) top-right, exceeding Leaden's amplitude; buffered cbb3/fix set (orange) near y=0; HutA at (+10.5, +2.2) is the most extreme point.\",\n    \"data_source\": \"REPORT.md §Finding 1; NB 01_leaden2018_fur_signature.ipynb cell 5\"\n  },\n  \"speaker_notes_seed\": \"This scatter is the S1 punchline figure. The x-axis is Leaden 2018's Δfur logFC for 93 published Δfur DEGs; the y-axis is our 4584-vs-4580 logFC for those same genes. Spearman ρ=0.315 (p=2.08e-03) and 71% sign concordance confirm that Fur derepression is a genuine component of our signal — we are seeing the canonical Fur regulon. The critical observation is the asymmetry: the concordant_strong cluster (dark blue, top-right) is amplified — our logFCs exceed Leaden's. HutA, the archetypal iron-derepressed TBDT, lands at our +10.5 vs Leaden's +2.2. The orange cluster (buffered cbb3/fix respiratory operon) sits near y=0 despite Leaden's -5 to -9 range — the SspB co-deletion is blunting that arm. This one panel sets up both findings that follow: Path A (concordant_strong, n=32) will test fitness enrichment; Path B (buffered, n=26) will fail enrichment against the 33.25% genome background.\",\n  \"evidence_anchors\": [\n    {\"kind\": \"report_section\", \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §Finding 1\"},\n    {\"kind\": \"report_section\", \"ref\": \"REPORT.md §NB01 — Leaden 2018 Fur signature\"}\n  ],\n  \"revision_log\": [\n    {\n      \"revised_at\": \"2026-06-07T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"finding_id\": \"F003\",\n      \"finding_class\": \"substory_arc\",\n      \"summary\": \"Replaced wrong-layer sphingolipid heatmap (00_sphingolipid_locus_heatmap.png, Layer 3 content duplicating slide 16/S3) with NB01 Fur-Leaden concordance scatter (NB01_fur_signature_scatter.png) as the S1 Layer-1 R-slide punchline figure (ρ=0.315, p=2.08e-03, 71% concordance, 93 DEGs); content replacement applied instead of canonical position-swap because the structural defect was wrong content occupying the S1 R-slide slot, not wrong slide position; slide 7 remains at position 7 in S1.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n","userModified":false}}
